# Forge — Your Personal Claude Code Toolkit

Built by Murtaza Bagwala. Type any skill below to get started.

---

## Available Skills

### `/browse` — Headless Browser
Automate any website: navigate, click, fill forms, take screenshots, assert state.
```bash
/browse goto https://example.com
/browse snapshot -i          # see all interactive elements
/browse screenshot /tmp/s.png
```

### `/probe` — QA & Testing
Run structured QA sessions on your app: smoke tests, regression checks, bug filing.
```bash
/probe
# → walks you through testing a feature end-to-end
```

### `/ship` — Shipping Workflow
Review your diff, write a great PR description, and ship — all in one flow.
```bash
/ship
# → runs pre-ship checks, writes PR, pushes
```

### `/audit` — PR Review
Deep code review with line-by-line comments, security checks, and improvement suggestions.
```bash
/audit
# → reviews the current PR or branch diff
```

### `/plan-product-review` — Product Plan Review
Review a product plan or spec from a PM/founder lens: clarity, scope, edge cases.
```bash
/plan-product-review
# → paste your spec and get structured feedback
```

### `/plan-eng-review` — Engineering Plan Review
Review a technical design doc: architecture, tradeoffs, risks, missing considerations.
```bash
/plan-eng-review
# → paste your design doc and get structured feedback
```

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# Test your app in a real browser
/browse goto https://localhost:3000

# Ship your current branch
/ship

# Review an open PR
/audit

# Run QA on a feature
/probe
```

---

## Tips

- `/browse` is the powerhouse — use it for any web interaction or verification task.
- `/ship` + `/audit` are the daily-driver workflow skills for PRs.
- `/probe` is great for structured QA before a release.
- `/plan-*` are for async review of documents and specs.

Type the skill name to begin. Each skill will guide you from there.
